<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Why plain English matters</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  GOV.UK recommends writing at a reading age of 9 to ensure content is accessible to everyone. Plain English:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>Reaches more people</strong> - 1 in 6 adults in the UK have poor literacy skills</li>
  <li><strong>Saves time</strong> - Clear content means fewer phone calls and emails</li>
  <li><strong>Builds trust</strong> - Residents appreciate straightforward communication</li>
  <li><strong>Improves accessibility</strong> - Helps people with cognitive disabilities, non-native speakers, and those reading on mobile</li>
</ul>

